This is my first time configuring my i3wm desktop, pardon me if there's anyhting missing: 

Required packages: 
-kitty (Terminal emulator)
-Thunar
-firefox
-xfce4-settings
-alsa
-mpd
-network-manager
-rofi-theme-selector
-btop
-picom
-i3wm

The polybar and rofi themes from these github repo:
https://github.com/adi1090x/polybar-themes
https://github.com/adi1090x/rofi

Theme used: Material
Inside material folder in polybar there're weather.sh (open-meteo API based on latitude and longitude) and weather_toggle.sh (time between each request to open meteo) that I wrote myself, change them based on what you want.

rofi-themes install at $HOME/.local/share/rofi; theme used: Dracula (Dracula1).
Dracula themes: https://draculatheme.com/rofi

i3 folder includes my own i3wm configuration and the background I used.

In kitty folder, there's an ascii file that I used to change the neofetch logo (How to change like what I did see neofetch article in ArchWiki).

For any problem using/configurating the polybar and rofi themes, use the hyperlinks above. 

Fonts needed: Fantasque Mono Sans, Noto Color Emoji, DejaVu Sans Mono
